<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Sorcerer<P>First an introduction. I play a level 50 Sorcerer; have experimented with the class a LOT. I am probably one of the first, if not THE first rank 4 Sorcerer. Does it mean we are a good class? No, it doesn't. It means I have a lot of time to play so my information should be quite valuable.<P>General: We have no buffs, we are a class of defense relying on nothing but reflexes, decisions, and all around skill to succeed. <BR>Because of this, to this day there are VERY FEW Sorcerers in DAOC. Our actions can drastically alter the state of a battle. Whatever happens to this class, PLEASE keep this play style intact. We are primarily defense and the weakest offensive caster of Albion. Remember, Albion cannot match the offensive power of Hibernia or Midgard, which I assume is the reason for our existence. <P>PvE: Not quite the most useful in early stages of the game. When I started playing back in October, we were not sought after for a group until the 30-50 range, period! This does however prove that if a group changes their style to accommodate a Sorcerer the results can be a safer hunt for everyone. A good Sorcerer will leave themselves at the greatest risk to attempt to keep battles as smooth as possible.<P>RvR: Now here is where things get tricky, and most unpleasant. While you can attempt to control the actions of a single group it is IMPOSSIBLE to rally everyone to your whim. Even the actions of another well-meaning Sorcerer could destroy your tactic and cause catastrophe. The same applies with a young player who strikes (and does not effect) the foe the Sorcerer has mesmerized causing them to be free and kill the Sorcerer.<P>Things only got worse from here as when stun/mez changes were weakened across the board this hit OUR class the hardest, THIS was a HUGE part of our defense!<P>Worse still DEBUFFS were also weakened across the board, taking away our only other method of a good defense!<P>Before the patches of the late these were often the only things stopping an enemy army from wiping our army out of existence! The result of this was the talented (and suicidal) Sorcerer being a feared and hated defensive player for Albion!<P>Currently, we have been made near useless ASIDE from a certain KEEP DEFENSE tactic that basically requires the keep to become almost lost and no more then a handful of allies to act at nearly the last moment! Already it has been proven there is an EASILY available method to prevent it! <P>Meanwhile enemy forces have the SAME spell effects readily available in INSANT cast form, which were the true bane of mesmerize & debuff! We carry in our arsenal NO stun or instant spells whatsoever.<P><BR>In Conclusion: Please take steps to repair the Sorcerer class and more specifically the Mind spec. Make them a viable player in defense for Albion once again. Thanks to the enemy archers and rogues it has never been difficult to kill us off quickly. Now we are killed by nearly ANY formidable enemy.<P><BR>Addendum & advice: I'd say the ONLY potentially overpowering features we once had were first to "chain mez" an opponent. Remember though mez breaks on any form of an attack. <P>The second was only in RARE circumstances where a Sorcerer could catch a few formidable players close together and defeat them one at a time with no help from the rest of Albion. The Sorcerer was in fact at great risk during the entire process not including the threat of other enemies nearby, and could only be achieved by the most skilled, dedicated, and lucky.<P>When resists are better implemented (Spellcrafting), it will definitely give the offending enemies a chance to avoid our tactics. Currently for already weak class this would be the final nail in the coffin.<P>It was always a safer bet to travel as hidden from sight as possible and not in direct link to the allied forces. Of course the drawback is there could be our death lurking even more hidden then us.<P>If the class were repaired to my specifications the worst possible outcome for our foes would make us a solo threat to enemy players under rare conditions for the most skillful. Considering the drastic increase in cost of power to go offensive (aside from our pet of course) and chance of failure (death), this would NOT be a viable tactic in any situation involving any more then VERY FEW players.<P>Thank you for your time, as I spent much of mine creating this post.<P>--------------------<P>ReincarnatedGod<P>"a chew toy of the demi-gods"
</FONT>
