<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
As a 34 Mind/35 Body I have no problems with our effectiveness in RvR.  I really doubt that a 44 Mind/30 Body sorc would have many problems either.  Basically trading 50 points on the DD, for a 1 foot wider ae mez and more str/con debuffed.  There are still many bugs they need to fix, but I'm thinking about how the game would be without them.  Lag/casting bugs are killing me much of time right now.<P>I do think they over-nerfed the str/con debuff.  I used to use the 34 version frequently.  Now I only use it at Keep defenses.  I know my 43 cleric(35 enhance spec) can buff 40-50 points higher than it's possible to debuff with the 40+ debuff spells.  The difficulty to cast the spells just doesn't match up to their current power.  Champions seem to only remove about 200 hps from me now from screenshots I've taken.  It's hard to really test debuffs on melee effectiveness in RvR.  If it lowers their damage output enough, which I doubt, then maybe it's not that bad.  <P>I have no problems with stun/mez nerfs compared to what they were when the game came out.  I think they poorly developed Stun/Mez for RvR in the game, and disagree with how they've changed it.  Diminishing returns needed to be fixed, and better resists implemented.  Possibly a heal chant breaking mez would've been a good solution.  That would allow people to use more tactics and strategy to combat mez. <P>Spec level also needs to matter more on the resist check.  I really don't think there's any negative in resist rates compared to a Sorc who put 10+ more points into it.  If someone chooses to spec Mind high there should be a benefit in resist rates, along with duration.<P>Mez is still my primary RvR tool and I'm still finding it very effective.<P>--------------------<P>Ierar<BR>50 Sorcerer Bedevere<BR>40 Body/34 Mind
</FONT>
